Project.Author: Jose Gomes
Project.Description:
Background

As a team we decided to build a web application that would benefit students. Our goal is to build a web application that students can use as a tool in their everyday lives to make their student life easier and more efficient.

We will be focusing on providing the best price for student essentials such as pens, notebooks, laptops, PC parts, kitchen appliances etc. We also aim to reach out to other student product providers (such as UNIDAYS) in hopes of providing the best possible prices from brands students may be looking to purchase from and allowing users to get the best deal available.

We hope to also implement a student housing section on our website which allows students to search from our range of Verified Student Accommodation. Our Verified Accommodation will be from verified reputable sources along with annual inspections of the properties to make sure such an environment is fit for a student. This will be possible only by allowing agencies to post their available student housing. This will help students by providing them a page to search for their accommodation to allow them to complete their course/degree. The page will have available housing for students that want to share a house, that will depend on the available housing posted by an agency.

The Home page will have a brief introduction of the website and what features and services it provides. It will include a navigation bar where the user can visit other subpages. The home page will also include useful information that a student or user would need. In addition to other ideas, we plan on implementing such as a guide section on our website which show students the essential services to apply for such the NHS, dentist, or reference websites such as “citethisforme” to make a student’s life easier.

Another idea we had was to have a section where we would have starter kits for students which would include, bedding and pillows to pots and pans to towels and shower gel at the best possible price. This idea led us to create more kits such as PC bundles (Which would have a variety of pc parts you can interchange and buy as a bundle), Laptop bundles (Which would include the option to choose from a variety of laptops recommended for students along with accessories such as laptop cases, backpacks etc.) and Hobby packs (which could include guitars, bikes, headphones, amps etc.)

We plan to develop a section on our website which students can sign up for a newswire regarding part time student jobs to full time after graduate Career options. We know students in their third year may find it stressful looking for a Career. We plan to make life easier for these students by creating a web form for students to give us their information so that we would take that information and research careers in their outlined field. Not only do we plan to develop this feature, but we also plan to contact various employers with ideal jobs for students to suggest that they post job vacancies on our “Looking for Work” section on our website to allow students to have a part time job during their education or after they have received their degree full time job.

An additional opportunity we have for our project is to create a Buy & Sell section on our website exclusive to students. Students can list items from clothes to old tech new students who have just enrolled who may not have the funds to purchases such items. This feature stops old belongings from going to waste in hopes of helping new students whilst helping old students.

We also planned on having a membership card that will provide users with an account that they could receive discounts on and new brand deals and more. The membership would offer a reward system for the users. By using our services, it will give users reward points or discounts and the more users use our services the more rewards they could receive. Having this feature could provide the reason for the user to use our services and bring more customers through referrals which will offer a reward to both end users.

Potential Homepage Motto:-

  1. Created by the students, made for the students, used by the students.

Features

This project will be created following the four basic database operations: CREATE, READ, UPDATE, DELETE. These operations are commonly known as CRUD.

Main Features:

  1. Sellers have access to Stock Control.
  2. Stock Control is a singular interface where the user can CREATE, UPDATE and DELETE items from the database.
  3. Customers have access to the homepage, listing and shopping cart.
  4. Homepage welcomes the user with messages and images.
  5. Listing uses the operation READ. This page retrieves data from the database and displays it to the costumer.
  6. Listing has a button to add the pretended amount of products to the shopping cart.
  7. The Shopping Cart has the option to remove products from an order.
  8. Providing an Accommodation searching service for students or other users
  9. Selling bundles of products depending on category such as kitchen, bathroom and more
  10. Provide a selling and purchasing page for users to sell or purchase their owned items for reuse.

Potential Features:

  1. Login system with different levels of permission.
  2. Dynamic homepage.
